(A×B)×{7} = {((2,5),7), ((2,6),7), ((3,5),7), ((3,6),7), ((4,5),7), ((4,6),7)}

2. A×(B×{7})

First, we need to find the Cartesian product B×{7}. This is the set of all ordered pairs (b, c) where b is in B and c is in {7}.

B×{7} = {(5,7), (6,7)}

Now, we need to find the Cartesian product of A×(B×{7}). This is the set of all ordered pairs (a, (b, c)) where a is in A and (b, c) is in B×{7}.

A×(B×{7}) = {(2,(5,7)), (2,(6,7)), (3,(5,7)), (3,(6,7)), (4,(5,7)), (4,(6,7))}

